children.comments:
Returns the bytes written indicating _partial_ success - for exact success, the written
bytes should equal the value's dynamic `byteLength`. This function should
strictly write to the `ArrayBuffer`, and shouldn't attempt to read from it.
children.title: putArrayBuffer

children.comments:
Returns the value parsed if successful.
This function should strictly read the `ArrayBuffer`, and shouldn't attempt to write to it.
children.title: readArrayBuffer

children.comments: Get the byte length of a value at runtime. Should be identical for read and written values.
children.title: byteLength

declarations.comments:
Generate a new `ArrayBuffer` from a value. Throws an `Error` if writing fails, or if the written bytes
do not equal the dynamic `byteLength` of the value.
declarations.title: encodeArrayBuffer

declarations.comments: Attempt to parse a value from an `ArrayBuffer`, starting at the first index.
declarations.title: decodeArrayBuffer

declarations.comments:
Determine a data type's byte length by walking its generic structure - note there is significant
overhead due to nested `Sum` types.
declarations.title: genericByteLength

declarations.comments:
Write data to an `ArrayBuffer` by walking its `Generic` structure - note this causes significant
overhead from nested `Sum` types.
declarations.title: genericPutArrayBuffer

declarations.comments:
Read data from an `ArrayBuffer` by building its `Generic` structure - note this causes significant
overhead from nested `Sum` types.
declarations.title: genericReadArrayBuffer

modules.name: Data.ArrayBuffer.Class.Types
modules.comments: Newtypes for the various bit-level numeric types.
